eu_initiatives:
Matikem is particularly interested in :  
-    RIS3 implementation and monitoring (strategic territorial approach, regional funding mechanisms & synergies of EU funds) 
-    Entrepreneurship fostering support; 
-    Definition of topics retained in workprogramms (e.g. NMBP / Bioeconomy/ COSME / INETRREG);   
-    Support for acquisition of financial sources (R&D and innovation supporting programs, private fundraisings, access to business angels etc.); 
-    Internationalisation of SMEs .

relevant_communication:
Since several years, Matikem participates in European Projects under Interreg, H2020 and COSME programs :  
-    The Tandem project (2013-2014) is a cross-border cooperation project funded under the INTERREG IV A FWV programme. It consisted of 17 Franco-Flemish partners, 5 fields of action corresponding to the Innovation Research Strategy for a Smart Specialisation (RIS3). As project partner, Matikem cluster assists the companies from Nord-Pas de Calais in the deployment of their innovation potential in the field of new materials, via cross-border 'tandems' with Flemish partners (Centexbel, VKC); 
-    Following the Tandem project, 5 partners including French and Belgium clusters (Matikem, UP-tex, Centexbel, POM West Vlaanderes, PlastiWin) launched the initiative The Region for Advanced Materials aiming at building a cross-border Meta cluster on the new materials domain. This project is now in construction. (https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=AtsZXeDDxzo);  
-    Synamera (2015-2017) is an EU project funded under the Horizon 2020 Program (CSA).  Synamera aims to improve the visibility for essential stakeholders, most notably national/regional programming and funding authorities, on programming synergetic actions between the European Union and Member States in the NMP Program.   (www.synamera.eu);  
-    ERICA (2016): Establishing RegIonal Cluster Agreement for sharing good practices in efficient and sustainable manufacturing. This project is composed of 4 European regions (Catalonia, Nord Pas de Calais-Picardie, Lombardy and South Netherlands). Each region is represented by a couple “cluster – technological center”. ERICA aims to highlight best practices in technology transfer, and to benefit directly to the companies and laboratories from the regional territories in all market applications related to the issues of sustainability of production methods. 

Parallel to European activities, we have just been developing our national strategy in close collaboration with our member’s community. Canada, the United States and Brazil are the countries we will target in our next action plan. As we already have strong collaboration with Canada and Brazil, we are now willing to strengthen the relationships with American stakeholders.
